eVol", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "vol", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "source_shape", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "target_shape", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "flatten", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "keep_range", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["only support numpy,sample vol, vol should be flatten 1D array without transpose\n\nArgs:\n    vol (_type_): _description_\n    source_shape (_type_): _description_\n    target_shape (_type_): _description_\n    flatten (bool, optional): _description_. Defaults to True.\n\nReturns:\n    _type_: _description_"]}, {"name": "src.utils.volumeUtils.normalizeVol", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "vol", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "outMin", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "outMax", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["normalize vol to [outMin,outMax], input vol should be numpy array\n\nArgs:\n    vol (ndarry): _description_\n    outMin (int, optional): _description_. Defaults to 0.\n    outMax (int, optional): _description_. Defaults to 1.\n\nReturns:\n    _type_: _description_"]}, {"name": "src.utils.volumeUtils.NormalizeDataInDir", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "dirPath", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "outMin", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "outMax", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "outDir", "type": null, "default": "..."}, {"name": "verbose", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Normalize the volume scalar data in dir, then save the normalized data in outDir\n\nArgs:\n    dirPath (_type_): the path to load unnormalize data\n    outMin (int, optional): min value after normalize. Defaults to 0.\n    outMax (int, optional): max value after normalize. Defaults to 1.\n    outDir (_type_, optional): the output dir which saved the normalized data. Defaults to \"None\" (which is dirPath).", "*